15:15.113 --> 15:21.763
According to some estimates that I've read, at 
least a third of all the heroin and marijuana used

15:15.113 --> 15:21.763
in the United States is supplied through Mexico. 
Do you think that this figure accurately reflects

15:25.062 --> 15:29.225
the Mexican drug threat? And do you think that this 
drug threat is increasing, or has it decreased

15:30.126 --> 15:40.075
over time,

15:30.126 --> 15:40.075
or not? I agree with the statistic, with the 
figure. I think it's about right. In fact, it may

15:45.180 --> 15:48.142
even be higher than that. I've heard that we get 
about 80% that we get in this country are either

15:52.388 --> 16:04.040
originate or are transferred through Mexico.

16:04.060 --> 16:04.260
80%. They don't grow cocaine in Mexico, but a lot of 
it comes through Mexico. They do grow opium poppy.

16:14.851 --> 16:20.657
We haven't seen much heroin here lately, but it's 
only because Cocaine is now the most popular drug.

16:30.973 --> 16:34.657
They grow a lot of marijuana in Mexico, as you know. 
And we see more marijuana than anything, even

16:36.219 --> 16:45.910
though the United States is now growing enough 
marijuana in its home that it probably doesn't

16:36.219 --> 16:45.910
need to be imported. But the new threat, from what I 
understand, is something that's just as

16:52.092 --> 17:03.762
dangerous, probably more dangerous even, than 
crack cocaine. And that is a crystalline

17:03.782 --> 17:14.452
substance that's derived from 
methamphetamines. It's coming from East Asia.

17:16.374 --> 17:17.434
It's coming from Korea. We haven't seen any of that 
here. yet, but if there's money in it, the Mexicans

17:21.775 --> 17:31.945
and the Latin Americans and South Americans are 
going to be involved in it. Methamphetamine is

17:31.965 --> 17:36.290
what they used to call speed. And this new form of it 
that's just been discovered out of Korea is

17:37.131 --> 17:44.959
finding its way into Hawaii. It's become already a 
major drug problem in Hawaii. And we're afraid

17:48.823 --> 17:51.225
it's going to find its way in the west coast and then 
the rest of the country. It gets back to this demand

17:57.340 --> 18:00.903
thing. It doesn't seem to matter what we do.

18:05.568 --> 18:11.013
There's always an element of the population that 
wants to do drugs.

18:13.656 --> 18:17.560
They want to do crap even though they know that it's 
dangerous and lethal. There are kids and young

18:22.137 --> 18:26.123
adults who want to do it. And the fact that we say 
it's bad, maybe even makes them want to do it, but I

18:26.143 --> 18:33.293
don't know why they want to do it. As long as that 
demand is there, there's going to be people who

18:33.313 --> 18:41.624
want to make money, and they're going to survive. 
So you think that some of these people, or the

18:42.766 --> 18:49.495
majority of these people, know that it's bad for 
them, but they do it anyway, or... I think they all

18:49.930 --> 18:51.132
do. I think they all do. They all know it's bad, but I 
think the peer pressure is such that it's almost

18:52.874 --> 19:00.223
irresistible.

19:05.610 --> 19:19.228
It's also glamorized, not so much as it used to be, 
but it's glamorized to some extent in movies, in

19:05.610 --> 19:19.228
