31:09.518 --> 31:17.648
that these aerostat balloons will make a big 
difference because They will see planes. The

31:19.663 --> 31:28.932
trouble, of course, is that you can't tell if a 
plane is going to cross the border until it

31:19.663 --> 31:28.932
actually does so.

31:32.736 --> 31:45.389
They can appear to be on radar, appear to be 
following the border, staying on the Mexican

31:32.736 --> 31:45.389
side, and then all of a sudden turn northward. And 
by the time that our radar operators pick it up and

31:49.201 --> 31:55.788
say, hey, a plane just came across. It's too late to 
go after him because he's already probably going

31:57.790 --> 32:08.380
to land in one of these out-of-the-way airports, 
and we're not going to be able to find him anywhere.

32:08.400 --> 32:11.544
I hope that's wrong, but that's sort of the way I 
feel. It's hard. That's our biggest threat, I

32:13.445 --> 32:18.010
think, probably with just almost impossible 
control. So other than the Airstat balloon, what

32:19.762 --> 32:30.733
other technological advances would you like to 
see here in McAllen?

32:33.275 --> 32:49.431
I wish we could find some electronic means of 
looking into cargo

32:33.275 --> 32:49.431
so we didn't have to unload trucks to find the 
contraband. The only way you can look into a cargo

32:49.917 --> 33:06.234
truck to see if there are drugs hidden either among 
the cargo or in the conveyance itself, that is in

32:49.917 --> 33:06.234
false walls of the truck, is on the ocean. And it 
takes two or three hours. There's damage done to

33:09.678 --> 33:13.963
the product. And we have to do this.

33:19.229 --> 33:35.333
gadget that could, a fluoroscope or x-ray, that 
could look into it and that you could tell whether

33:19.229 --> 33:35.333
there was anything going on there, that would 
probably be

33:19.229 --> 33:35.333
a real help to us. But I think the technology is 
probably available for that sort of thing, but

33:35.353 --> 33:47.751
it's so expensive it's only people can afford it, 
people like the Saudi Arabians. They have those

33:49.233 --> 33:53.437
sorts of things on a test basis. I understand 
there's a big machine made in France that Saudi

33:53.517 --> 34:06.469
Arabia had bought to take a look at cargo coming 
into their country. But

34:06.769 --> 34:18.700
as far as I know, it hasn't been effective enough to 
be cost effective as far as I know. I think they'd

34:19.051 --> 34:22.695
pay almost anything to do the work. But they're not 
reliable. But I remember for years Custom Service

34:26.179 --> 34:36.651
has tried to find things that would save them time 
in looking for dope. We've had electronic

34:38.072 --> 34:41.236
sniffing machines at airports. We've done major 
tests in the United States at airports. Ones that

34:46.302 --> 34:48.484
would sniff suitcases that came through it from 
there, across it from there. We had one machine,

34:55.435 --> 35:02.783
yes, that would show an alarm that there were drugs 
in it. We had another machine that we tested that

35:02.823 --> 35:19.180
would, it was hidden inside a

35:02.823 --> 35:19.180
tabletop or counter like in an airport. passenger 
arrives from overseas and picks up his bags. And

35:24.254 --> 35:27.017
the first person he talks to is an immigration 
officer. He sort of bellies up to this counter on

35:28.359 --> 35:38.393
the other side of which is an immigration officer 
and hands him his passport. There was a machine

35:38.473 --> 35:49.588
that supposedly would sniff this person as he got 
close and could tell whether he had been handling

35:38.473 --> 35:49.588
or had any on him These gadgets were so unreliable 
that I reckon they gave up on all of them because I

35:50.092 --> 36:02.706
haven't heard anything about them in a long time. 
I'm beginning to think maybe there is no

36:02.726 --> 36:12.397
way to really look except just tearing things 
apart and looking with the naked eye. Detected

36:12.797 --> 36:13.959
dogs do that. That's probably our best Yeah,

36:16.957 --> 36:34.721
but I don't think they worked out because they 
don't have them now. I remember when they were

