Customs Service more efficient in combating 
drugs on Mexican

36:43.771 --> 36:58.489
plants? What aspects of inspector training would 
you improve in order to make the Customs Service

36:58.509 --> 37:08.862
more efficient at combating drugs on Mexican 
plants? Well, I think the most important thing we

37:10.973 --> 37:17.541
can teach new inspectors would be, I don't even 
know if it's something we can teach. It's a matter

37:17.601 --> 37:22.507
of attitude.

37:22.527 --> 37:32.720
We need inspectors who have a commitment to law 
enforcement and a dedication to public service.

37:35.543 --> 37:37.366
And I don't think you can teach that to people. 
There are other kinds of people you go after. but

37:40.302 --> 37:47.531
people take jobs for all kinds of reasons.

37:48.292 --> 37:56.082
Those reasons being probably

37:48.292 --> 37:56.082
important, but they're not important to a lot of 
people. A lot of people take the job because they

37:56.102 --> 38:08.458
pay well, they're steady, in an area where minimum 
wage is really the real problem. You have people

38:08.478 --> 38:09.820
who... After a few years, we made very good money as 
customs officers. There was a certain amount of

38:17.099 --> 38:21.725
stature involved. They recognized members of the 
community.

38:28.114 --> 38:40.971
But if I could teach them anything, I would want to 
teach them

38:28.114 --> 38:40.971
just dedication, integrity, integrity, 
integrity. And I just don't know if you can keep

38:41.153 --> 38:44.138
your mind. We hope we get those people and we 
reinforce it, those who haven't, I think. Because

38:52.572 --> 38:58.221
there are a lot of temptations out

38:52.572 --> 38:58.221
here. They claim there are temptations. I've been 
in the service 25 years and no one's ever offered me

39:00.004 --> 39:06.655
that. And yet... If it happens, I know it happens, 
because this happened right here in this

39:09.065 --> 39:20.297
apartment. I was thinking about

39:20.477 --> 39:33.671
integrity. I do have a question here about it. I'm 
sorry. Oh, no, it's fine. So you do see that the

39:39.187 --> 39:47.814
integrity is a real, the perceived problem is a 
real problem. How much of this do you see, and has it

39:47.975 --> 39:52.519
increased, the rate of which? And what do you think 
is the main cause of the integrity problem? Well, I

39:56.122 --> 39:59.004
see integrity as a problem. I don't know what you 
mean by a real problem. I think the percentage of

40:02.787 --> 40:08.012
officers who

40:10.979 --> 40:14.385
who do things illegal out here is very, very small. 
I really do. I think it's a problem. But in the whole

40:17.811 --> 40:23.019
scheme of custom, it's a minor problem. We've had a

40:23.039 --> 40:33.677
couple of people arrested here, inspectors. The 
reason I'm saying this is I'm trying to answer the

40:33.697 --> 40:37.003
question about what causes it, and I don't know 
what causes it. Since I've been here in Hidalgo,

40:44.741 --> 40:56.878
and this is a big port, I have to go on record as 
saying this is a major port of entry, even though

40:44.741 --> 40:56.878
nobody ever heard of Hidalgo, who's not from this 
area. The port of Hidalgo is one of the biggest

40:56.898 --> 41:01.745
ports on the Mexican border. There are maybe two or 
three in the whole border that are bigger. We have

41:08.540 --> 41:32.128
about

41:08.540 --> 41:32.128
100 employees here, customs,

41:08.540 --> 41:32.128
of whom, well not 100, we have about 90, of whom 75 
are inspectors, and we're about 20 short from what

41:08.540 --> 41:32.128
we are right now. Immigration service has another 
50. The agriculture has another 25. We bring in $50

41:37.126 --> 41:41.692
million a year in revenue. We have a payroll of, I 
don't know what our payroll is, but our officers,

41:43.495 --> 41:59.556
our 80 officers, between them, earned over a 
million and a half dollars just in overtime last

41:43.495 --> 41:59.556
year. And the overtime is about $20.

42:05.510 --> 42:08.594
less than 10% of their total earnings. So it's a 
major operation. Getting back to what I started to

42:12.599 --> 42:24.694
say, since I've been here, we've lost about seven 
or eight officers for what I would call breaches of

42:12.599 --> 42:24.694
integrity. Integrity lapses, or however you want 
to say it. Of those,

42:34.973 --> 42:40.980
Only three were actually indicted for criminal 
activity. Every one of those three

42:42.802 --> 43:04.187
was targeted by Internal Affairs because 
somebody called them and said, I think this guy is

42:42.802 --> 43:04.187
doing drugs or is dishonest or is doing something 
illegal. They don't target them unless somebody

43:05.230 --> 43:14.905
calls and tells them that they're suspicious. And 
they respond. In every one of these cases, two of

43:17.729 --> 43:32.672
the three cases, they gave these people who they 
had been told are dirty, as we say, they gave them

43:17.729 --> 43:32.672
the opportunity They said, well, we'll find out if 
they are guilty. And they gave them opportunities

43:35.688 --> 43:38.411
to break the law. And they did. Two of them did. Two 
of them actually took bribes. One of whom has been

43:45.841 --> 43:47.262
convicted.

43:49.786 --> 43:51.288
I shouldn't say they actually took them. I should 
say they allegedly took them. One of whom has been

43:54.412 --> 43:56.935
convicted of two counts of bribery. The other is 
about to go to trial on the same charges plus

43:57.576 --> 44:02.642
others, plus other charges. All the charges stem 
from the investigation conducted by the Attorney

44:04.816 --> 44:15.970
of Affairs then providing the opportunity for 
these guys to break the law and they broke the law.

44:16.511 --> 44:17.412
Perfectly legal. I'm not saying this in any 
derogatory sense. I'm in favor of this kind of law

44:21.237 --> 44:28.786
enforcement because we find out who the dishonest 
people are. The third of these three was

44:29.647 --> 44:34.013
acquitted.

44:34.600 --> 44:40.466
on drugs, on bribery, it was on passing an illegal 
alien. Now, he was acquitted of that in court, and

44:40.486 --> 44:45.891
he's trying to get his job back. I don't know 
whether he will or not, but I have no opinion on

44:46.071 --> 44:55.540
whether he should be coming back or not. The other 
five of that group of eight resigned in every case

45:05.330 --> 45:20.649
under some kind of suspicion,

45:05.330 --> 45:20.649
in most cases because they were consorting with 
known criminals, even though there was no

45:05.330 --> 45:20.649
specific charges against them. One person 
resigned because he was offered a bribe, didn't

45:22.451 --> 45:32.603
take the bribe, but didn't report to internal 
affairs that he was a prophet of God. And so they

45:38.541 --> 45:49.517
confronted him with that and then he decided to 
resign and then go through trial and so on. But all

45:49.537 --> 46:02.877
of these, if in trying to sort out what these people 
all had in common, it's difficult without

46:06.400 --> 46:12.166
making almost making an ethnic slur because all of 
them are locals. All of them are Mexican

46:13.688 --> 46:14.950
Americans. All of them have contacts on both sides 
of the border. All of them grew up in this area.

46:24.741 --> 46:35.833
And all of them, as I say, have friends, relatives,

46:24.741 --> 46:35.833
some of whom have contacts with It's

46:37.703 --> 46:54.297
not

46:37.703 --> 46:54.297
to say that every local person is a potential 
criminal. It's not to say at all, but that seems to

46:54.317 --> 46:57.163
be the problem.

